definitions.definition: To split from or to withdraw from membership of a political union, an alliance or an organisation .
To split or to withdraw one or more constituent entities from membership of a political union, an alliance or an organisation .

main_definition: ( intransitive ) To split from or to withdraw from membership of a political union, an alliance or an organisation .
secondary_definitions: ( transitive , uncommon ) To split or to withdraw one or more constituent entities from membership of a political union, an alliance or an organisation .
